race.comment: ROMA GREEN (2) showed good early dash on debut and stalked the pace last start before drawing clear to score by half a length at Bathurst. Is sure to have come on with that run under his belt and can make it two on the trot. BUSHWALKER (7) has been racing in great heart including another narrow minor placing here at the latest.. Best figures measure up and is sure to run well again. VINCENTVANGEE (14) is a son of Smart Missile on debut for the O'Halloran stable. Fitter for two trials and will likely attract market support. Keeping safe. SILVER CHAIR (8) was much better last time when beaten narrowly at Dubbo after leading them up. Not without her chance with a similar effort.
